{
  "stem": "10572.7",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And ultimately I said to Medlach one day-- and I said, now let's move this camouflage and start to teach ethics and start to teach religion and so on.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The thing that I got a big kick out of that was-- one day there was a pastor who had come to Camp Ashby, an American pastor, and who told me after a couple of Sundays that he couldn't waste this time on those four guys who that came to church to him.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when we had ultimately hundreds of these people there, I called him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said, you know if you have free time on the next Sunday, why don't you come to Camp Ashby?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I would like to show you something.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I took him to the church services of Camp Ashby.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he sat there and he says, I don't believe this.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I said, what do you mean?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He said how did this happen?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I said, you know, Pastor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I said, I'm Jewish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He said, yeah, i know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I said 2,000 years ago, another Jew tried to teach you what later on became Christianity.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's all I did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And ultimately I was transferred out of Camp Ashby and transferred to Third Service Command headquarters in Baltimore into counterintelligence.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we formed a team of five agents who somehow had a little bit of the same background as I had.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had one fellow from Holland, a Jewish boy from Holland, and others who were trained and trained to become interrogators and do political classification of prisoners, and that-- do political classification so that AMG, Allied Military Government, could use our classification done in the place of an American POW camp for reconstruction of Germany.",
      "word_count": 55
    }
  ],
